\pard\fs24\lang2057\f1\fs27\cf1\b\ltrpar\ql\sb450\sa45\li150\ri45 Q1.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li567\ri567 Dastan\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 Dastan is a two-player game in which each player takes turns to move one of their five pieces on a six-by-six square grid. Each player has one mirza (ruler) and four standard pieces. Each player has a kotla (fortress).\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 The winner is the player who has the highest score when the game ends. The game ends when a player manages to move their mirza into the square containing the opponent\u8217?s kotla or they capture the opponent\u8217?s mirza.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 The starting position of the game is shown in \b Figure 1\b0 . Player one\u8217?s mirza piece is represented by 1, their other pieces by ! and their kotla by K. Player two\u8217?s mirza piece is represented by 2, their other pieces by " and their kotla by k. Row numbers are shown on the left-hand side and column numbers at the top.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b\ltrpar\qc\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0 Figure 1\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0 \~\par

