\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\b\ltrpar\qc\sb270\sa90\li45\ri45 Cuirassier\par
\intbl\qc\sb90\sa90\li45\ri45{\pict\jpegblip\picw2385\pich2400\picwgoal2385\pichgoal2400\picscalex100\picscaley100
}
\intbl \cell
\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb270\sa90\li45\ri45 The \b cuirassier\b0  (armoured cavalry with a musket) move option means a piece can move either one or two squares forward, or two squares horizontally followed by one square forward from its current position.
\intbl \cell\pard\intbl\row\pard
\pard
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 In the game, there is an offer that contains a move option. Before moving a piece, a player can choose to take the move option from the offer, replacing one of the move options in their queue with it. A new move option will then be generated for the offer.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 Each player starts the game with a score of 100. Their score decreases when they:\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~move a piece \u8211? the amount of the decrease is based on how near the front of the queue the chosen move option was\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~take the move option from the offer \u8211? the amount of the decrease is based on how near the front of the queue the replaced move option was.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567\fi0 Their score increases if:\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~they capture an opponent\u8217?s piece (by 1) or an opponent\u8217?s mirza (by 5)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~one of their pieces or their mirza is occupying the same square as a kotla (by 5 for their own kotla; by 1 for their opponent\u8217?s).\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567\fi0 Figure 3\b0  shows the first few turns of a sample game.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b\ltrpar\qc\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0 Figure 3\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0 \~\par

